Package: subid
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: peer-to-peer network based digital currency - daemon
 subi is an experimental new digital currency that enables instant, private
 payments to anyone, anywhere in the world. subi uses peer-to-peer
 technology to operate with no central authority: managing transactions
 and issuing money are carried out collectively by the network. subi Core
 is the name of the open source software which enables the use of this currency.
 .
 This package provides the daemon, subid, and the CLI tool
 subi-cli to interact with the daemon.

Package: subi-qt
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: peer-to-peer network based digital currency - Qt GUI
 subi is an experimental new digital currency that enables instant, private
 payments to anyone, anywhere in the world. subi uses peer-to-peer
 technology to operate with no central authority: managing transactions
 and issuing money are carried out collectively by the network. subi Core
 is the name of the open source software which enables the use of this currency.
 .
 This package provides subi-Qt, a GUI for subi based on Qt.

Package: subi-tx
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: peer-to-peer digital currency - standalone transaction tool
 subi is an experimental new digital currency that enables instant, private
 payments to anyone, anywhere in the world. subi uses peer-to-peer
 technology to operate with no central authority: managing transactions
 and issuing money are carried out collectively by the network. subi Core
 is the name of the open source software which enables the use of this currency.
 .
 This package provides subi-tx, a command-line transaction creation
 tool which can be used without a subi daemon.  Some means of
 exchanging minimal transaction data with peers is still required.
